review_blob: As for Dry beers go, i probably have to shove this in the "weird" section, it has that strange taste to it. i'm not sure whether it's a good thing or a bad thing, but it's definatly a "thing". now that i've basically crapped on about nothing ill say this beer is about the worst "dry" beer i've ever had, Tooheys Extra dry is way better than this beer, and thats saying alot, cause i'm no big fan of that beer either. Tastes of chemicals and not much else really.

and in a move that would make practically ever serious beer lover baulk at the knees, CUB adds a shot a vodka in their bland range of beer in order to get the young and hip crowds drunk faster. Now all they need is a bottle with a wider neck and this beer is complete.

Fruity smell, kinda average with a poor thin head. Nice hops flavour coming through, but it seemed to me ths beer was lacking a few things to make it worth my while, i'll drink it again, but i'm not going to go out of my way in order to get some.

The first smell, i kinda stuick my nose in a little too far, and sniffed a little to hard, and i thought my nose was going to fall off, just the way i like it. Yeasty, champagne like, ciderish.
Taste is spicey, hops are well presents, nicelty carbonated.
I quite liked this beer, i'll have it again, and again, and again.
Not Much can be said about this beer that hasn't been said before, but i'll keep typing anyway. peppery, fruity, heaps of flavour. i really enjoy this beer, and i don't drink it often enough.
If you ever get the chance to try this Pilsener on tap, give it a go, I was pleasently suprised how much better it tasted from the tap than from the bottle, refreshing, could be drank all night.

Like all of James Squire beers, it's far far better out of the tap than out of the bottle. Nutty, Citrus, Grassy characters, You can certainly taste the Alcohol in it, but for this beers it's quite refreshing.
A great session beer.
beer_name: James Squire Nine Tales Amber Ale

review_blob: Maybe i've been getting bad batches or something, but this is my least favourite Malt Shovel Brew, i can tolerate it, and i enjoy it, but not like the others.Taste is quite average, quite crisp, and bitter, but in my opinion it suffers from a lack of Hops. It's quite average on my drinkability scale.

Sweet Sweet Candy. Well not really, but a dam fine beer, lovely hop flavour, one of my fondest memories was having a case of this stuff in my bedroom, and waking with the taste of Little Creatures on my lips, cracked one open before i got out of bed, sure it was warm. but hey who cares. Tastes of Hops, Lemon, etc. a great fine beer. A beer that turns you into a Alcoholic for no other reason but the taste.

Tooheys have the Ability to produce utter crap, luckily they got at least 1 beer right. That beer is Tooheys Old. While it's not a fantastic brew, it's certainly not bad either. Small Tastes of Chocolat, Smaller tastes of coffee, malty, etc. Bland, but extremely drinkable

In this eviewers Humble opinion, this beer suffers from a lack of Alcohol Content. Given an extra percent it could have given it more of a kick with the flavour department. Slightly hoppy, tastes a little bit like berrys.
Water. More Flavour please.

Malt Shovel tried hard with this limited release brew, and they did a good god, but it seems as they fell a little bit short. Hazy appearnce with little head, tastes of Babana, clove, Chinese Ya Pear flavour believe it or not. It's a good brew that i'd drink again if i could get some.
Although This porter isn't as flavoured as most. I still enjoyed this drop. Tastes of Malt, Chocolate, small tastes of Coffee. I'll drink this again, and again.
beer_name: James Squire Jack of Spades Porter

review_blob: Once again with Monteith's beers, the head dies really fast, inoffensive, bland, slightly hoppy, a bit burnt, slightly artificial with some chemicals present, I would drink this again. Decent beer.

Froths up like a mother hubbard the second you open one. Like you would want to ever open one in the first place. Tastes prety much just like every other Tooheys Product, except this one extra carbonated, and sold off as a "Premium" beer. Flavourless. Don't get me wrong, it's drinkable, but for all the wrong reasons.

Naked Ale is definatly my favourite Masthead brew that i have tasted so far. Smells like an average German Wheat, looks like an average German Wheat, Tastes like an average German Wheat. Nice long lasting frothing head. Could have done with a little more flavour though. I'll drink it again.

Average beer really, looks decent although the head dies fast. I thought it was strange that it was 7%abv, yet i couldn't taste much alcohol if any, and it's even stranger that with not much flavour i still couldn't taste the alcohol. It's not a bad beer at all. It's quite drinkable, but with so many better beers on the market it's really not worth the effort.

This beer kinda annoyed me, being my first Honey Wheat, i wasn't expecting much, because i thought the two would not go together. I did not enjoy this brew at all, although i remember myself thinking "you didn't like Stouts the first time you drank one either, give it a go". Well by the end of the beer i still didn't like it, although it did improve a little when it warmed a bit. Tastes of Honey or course, but as for the wheat beer, i couldn't taste that it was a wheat for some reason. 

Overall, bland wheat with honey added to "try" to inhance the flavour.
Probably CUB's best beer, Pours a ecent thick head when it wants to. Nice Roasted malty flavour. Almost too sweet for my likings, but just saves itself. It's a semi-decent session beer.
Duff is right, little flavour, very watery, nice creamy head though. Extremely boring beer

Nice looking dark amber ale, a bit reddish, smells nicely malty, slightly roasted nice foamy head. Tastes is very roasted, almost too roasted for my taste. Still it's a good beer that i'll be drinking again when i can. Not great, but drinkable.

It's better than your average Macro Swill thats for sure, but still falls short of being a good beer. Nice creamy head, not overly carbonated like most Macros can be. Taste is a little skunky, but thats to be expected from these damm green bottles. It's not the best lager on the market, but it's definatly not the worst.
